OL,3,C'This isn't Castlereagh': Ministers
OL,4,Cwarned over answering questions
OL,6,F"Therefore, any questions relating to
OL,7,Fexpenditure are a matter for the
OL,8,FOmbudsman's office."
OL,10,FThe Speaker said: "Ministers should
OL,11,Frecognize that they are answerable to
OL,12,Fthe members of this House, who are
OL,13,Fanswerable to the Northern Ireland
OL,14,Fpublic and if they're sitting on
OL,15,Fanswers that they know they have and
OL,16,Fare withholding information, they are
OL,17,Fshowing disrespect to the community in
OL,18,FNorthern Ireland.
